other_tests.procedure_name: Histologic studies and culture of ovarian tissue
other_tests.findings: Cellularity of the stroma retained, few follicles with one or two layers of granulosa cells present.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Six pieces of ovarian tissue produced increasing amounts of estradiol, progesterone, and testosterone when cultured.

other_tests.procedure_name: Light-microscopical analysis of thick blood smears
other_tests.findings: 1 to 10 P. malariae parasites per 100 fields.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Parasitemia resolved by day 2 after treatment.

other_tests.findings: Major coronary rupture occurred after high-pressure balloon inflation.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Successful sealing of rupture with a polytetrafluoroethylene-coated stent; patient had an uneventful recovery.
